ZCZC EE45
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 052300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND NE FM THE AZORES
HIGH THROUGH MUCH OF THE NITON FCST AREA BUT WITH LOWER PRESSURE BRINGING
A MORE CYCLONIC AIRFLOW TO NWERN PARTS. THE RIDGE IS THEN LIKELY TO DECLINE
A LITTLE THROUGH TUESDAY ALLOWING THE MORE CYCLONIC FLOW IN THE NW TO EXTEND
FURTHER E. THERE ARE THEN SOME UNCERTAINTIES FOR WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY
BUT CURRENT INDICATIONS ARE FOR THE RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE TO PERSIST THROUGH
MUCH OF THE FCST AREA BUT WITH A LARGE ATLANTIC LOW MAINTAINING THE CYCLONIC
FLOW ACROSS THE FAR NW. NO GALES ARE CURRENTLY FCST THROUGH THIS PERIOD
BUT WITH STRG WINDS PERHAPS DEVELOPING IN THE NW OF THE NITON AREA ON THURSDAY.
OCCASIONAL FOG BANKS AREA ALSO PROB THROUGH THE SW APPROACHES ENGLISH CHANNEL
AND SERN N SEA DURING THE PERIOD
